## UI/UX Consistency (Design System)

- **Use tokens, not ad-hoc colors**: prefer Tailwind semantic tokens (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-card`, `border-border`, `bg-muted`, `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-primary`, `text-primary-foreground`).
- **Dark mode is mandatory**: every new UI must be readable in `.dark`.
  - Avoid very low opacity surfaces (`*/20`, `*/30`) for primary containers/cards.
  - Primary CTA must have strong contrast (button background vs label).
- **Use existing primitives**: prefer `Button`, `Input`, `Card`, `Alert`, `TextLink`, `Checkbox` instead of custom HTML styling.
- **Auth screens pattern**:
  - Centered container, `max-w-md`, card `rounded-2xl`, padding `p-8`, clean spacing (`gap-5`, `mt-8`).
  - Logo/brand: prefer `AppLogoIcon` (SVG) in UI; avoid raster logos with baked backgrounds.
- **Typography & hierarchy**:
  - Title: `text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-balance`
  - Description/help: `text-sm text-muted-foreground text-balance`
- **Forms UX**:
  - Disable inputs/buttons while `processing`.
  - Show success/status using `Alert`; show field errors with `InputError`.
  - Keep primary CTA full-width.
